      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Interesting race - three former Victorians and two former New South Welshmen. PAFITIS (2) is a former Victorian who was runner-up at his last run there at Colac. Best figures stack up and placed 3/3 while fresh. Expected to go close. RIVERS OF BABYLON (4) is also a former Victorian who has started once this area and ran very well, narrowly missing behind Good Onya Darl who was in the previous race. Has pace and will take catching. MERIMBULA (1) hasn't raced since March when safely held over 2007m at Kilmore. Well back in trip for Territory debut but can hit the line hard fresh. FORGING AHEAD (3) has raced in both NSW and Queensland and makes debut for the new yard. Has run well fresh and worth including.",
